The first step of our analyses revealed that month of collection was significantly associated with variation in measurements in six cases (tarsus length – 1 species, wing length – 3 species, Kipp – 2 species; 
  Table 1). Sex was significantly associated with the morphological traits in 13 (tarsus length – 4 species, wing length – 8 species, Kipp – 1 species; 
  Table 1) and age in 16 cases (wing length – 8 species, Kipp – 8 species; 
  Table 1) respectively.
